section.section:
The board shall serve as the governing body of the cabinet and shall exercise all powers and authorities conferred upon it by statute, including, but not limited to, the following functions:
Strategic planning;
Finance;
Business assistance;
Marketing and promotion;
Community development;
Workforce development;
Innovation; and
All economic development powers and authorities not specifically conferred by statute to another agency or authority of state government.

text.section:
By no later than thirty (30) days after July 14, 1992, the governing bodies of each of the following organizations shall meet and nominate two (2) persons from each of the six (6) Congressional districts of the Commonwealth and two (2) persons from the state at large, as candidates for the initial appointment as private sector members to the board:
The Kentucky Industrial Development Council;
The Associated Industries of Kentucky;
The Kentucky State AFL-CIO;
The Kentucky Farm Bureau Federation;
The Kentucky Chamber of Commerce; and
The Kentucky Economic Development Corporation.
